text.section:
An applicant is entitled to receive the commercial driver's license applied for if the applicant:
Passes the examination required by this subtitle;
Is eligible to drive pursuant to the Commercial Driver's License Information System and the National Driver Register;
Surrenders any previously issued commercial driver's instructional permit or license; and
Pays the fees prescribed by this subtitle.

Each commercial driver's license issued by the Administration shall:
Be marked "commercial driver's license" or "CDL"; and
Include the following information:
The licensee's:
Full name and current mailing address;
Physical description including sex, height, and weight;
Color photograph or photo-image;
The date of issuance;
The date of expiration; and
Any other information required by the Code of Federal Regulations or the Administration.
